        <title>RFC 4830: Problem Statement for Network-Based Localized Mobility Management (NETLMM), J. Kempf</title>
        <dc:date>2007-04-01T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>Localized mobility management is a well-understood concept in the IETF, with a number of solutions already available.  This document looks at the principal shortcomings of the existing solutions, all of which involve the host in mobility management, and makes a case for network-based local mobility management.  This memo provides information for the Internet community. </description>
    </item>

